snippet.textDisplay:
Oh Mykie....You wanna hear a true "Shitty little Tale"?
At least yours wasn't passed around during family gatherings.

* Warning, it's long *


When I was four or five, I got to go to Disney world and Sea world. It was the best time of my life, especially when I got to experience the Alien Encounter ride that Disney World had at the time.
Suffice to say, I was a monster that was made when my Dad snuck baby me into the Alien trilogy reruns that he refused to miss at the movies, making a nightmare baby that enjoyed horror movies more than children shows (except for Popeye and the Simpsons).


It was our second stay at Disney World and my Sis and I managed to get my Dad to promise a second visit to Alien Encounter. We were in the line when I suddenly needed to desperately go to the toilet, but I refused to say anything and ended up doing the 'I can hold my pee dance', my Dad knowing what I was doing, ordered my Sis who was six years older than I was, so 10-11, to take me to the loo. She was pissed, so she grabs my arm and just drags me to where the portable toilets were and refused to look at me.


Now, that toilet was the worst I have ever been in but at the time I was desperate, so I decided to brave the shit smeared area and try and hover over the toilet while holding up my shorts so they wouldn't touch the floor. I ended up peeing on the shit floor which I then slipped on in my panic to get closer to the toilet, I fell into the toilet and got stuck. I can't remember how I managed to get out but by the time I did, I was covered in shit and my own piss. I tried to wipe the worst of it off before getting out in hope that no one would get in my way to see the ride again. My Sis, still in her quest to not look at me, grabbed my timid hand I had offered and dragged me back to the line. I remember the double take my Dad did before he yelled at my sister, "Jesus Christ Erin, I asked you to take her to the toilet not dunk her in it!". After that, it was a little hazy as I spent the rest of the night crying because my Dad had to take me back to the hotel for a bath and a change of clothes, coming back to Disney World in time for the fireworks but Alien Encounter was closed....The line we had been in was the second last before it closed for the day. It was also our last day before setting off to Sea World.


I still wish for another viewing of Alien Encounter, best Disney ride ever.

***Jesus uses demonic forces to rebuke and chasten us so that we REPENT....

* (REPENTANCE)***

(Greek. Metanoia); Strong's #3341; This Greek word is a compound word derived from meta, meaning "after" and suggesting some type of change, and nous, meaning "mind."

Thus the word strictly denotes "a change of mind."

But it also connotes remorse for sin, accompanied by a desire to turn away from one's sin, to God, for salvation.

Both John the Baptist and Jesus began their ministries with a call to repentance. (See Matthew 3:2, 4:17)---A call that many of the social outcasts and "sinners" of that day answered, (See Luke 19:1-10),

but that the religious people rejected. (Luke 11:39-44; 18:9-14).
